## ASTRO RULES

- Use `.astro` for UI components and pages.
- Use `client:visible` for interactive islands (lazy hydration).
- Use `client:idle` for non-critical interactive components.
- NEVER use `client:load` except for critical above-the-fold elements.
- Prefer pure Astro components (zero JS) whenever possible.
- `getStaticPaths()` for all dynamic routes.
- Always explicitly declare `export const prerender = true` on static pages.
- Call data service functions inside page frontmatter, not inside components.

```astro
---
// pages/projects/[slug].astro
import { getProjectBySlug, getProjects } from '@/lib/data/projects';
import type { Project } from '@/types';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const projects = await getProjects();
  return projects.map((p) => ({ params: { slug: p.slug }, props: { project: p } }));
}

interface Props { project: Project; }
const { project } = Astro.props;
---
```

---

## TAILWIND CSS RULES

- Use utility classes. NEVER inline CSS for static values.
- Use `@apply` sparingly and only in `global.css` for recurring patterns.
- Mobile-first breakpoints: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`, `2xl:`
- Custom palette and fonts defined in `tailwind.config.mjs` using CSS variables.
- Use `clsx` + `cn()` helper for conditional classes.
- Semantic class grouping: layout → spacing → sizing → typography → visual → interactive.

```astro
<!-- ✅ Correct: mobile-first, semantic grouping -->
<div class="flex flex-col gap-4 p-4 md:flex-row md:gap-8 md:p-8">

<!-- ❌ Incorrect: desktop-first, unorganized -->
<div class="lg:flex-row p-8 flex-col gap-4 lg:gap-8 flex lg:p-4">
```

---

## SEO — MANDATORY RULES

### BaseLayout.astro must ALWAYS include:

```astro
---
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description: string;
  image?: string;
  canonicalURL?: string;
  type?: 'website' | 'article';
  publishedDate?: string;
}
const { title, description, image, canonicalURL, type = 'website' } = Astro.props;
const canonical = canonicalURL ?? Astro.url.href;
---
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

  <!-- Primary Meta -->
  <title>{title} | [Your Name] — Full-Stack Developer</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description} />
  <meta name="author" content="[Your Name]" />
  <meta name="robots" content="index, follow" />
  <link rel="canonical" href={canonical} />

  <!-- Open Graph -->
  <meta property="og:type" content={type} />
  <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
  <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
  <meta property="og:image" content={image} />
  <meta property="og:url" content={canonical} />
  <meta property="og:locale" content="en_US" />

  <!-- Twitter Card -->
  <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
  <meta name="twitter:title" content={title} />
  <meta name="twitter:description" content={description} />
  <meta name="twitter:image" content={image} />

  <!-- Structured Data -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(personSchema)} />

  <!-- Font preconnects -->
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />

  <!-- Favicon set -->
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
  <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/apple-touch-icon.png" />
  <link rel="manifest" href="/site.webmanifest" />
</head>
```

### JSON-LD Person schema (in src/data/siteConfig.ts):

```typescript
export const personSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "[Your Name]",
  "jobTitle": "Full-Stack Developer & Engineering Manager",
  "url": "https://[your-domain].com",
  "sameAs": [
    "https://linkedin.com/in/[profile]",
    "https://github.com/[username]"
  ],
  "knowsAbout": [
    "Java", "TypeScript", "React", "AstroJS",
    "Scrum", "Project Management", "Django", "REST APIs"
  ]
};
```

### Per-page SEO rules:

- Unique meta description on every page: 150–160 characters.
- One H1 per page → H2 for sections → H3 for subsections.
- Descriptive slugs in English: `/projects/kanban-metrics-dashboard`.
- Descriptive `alt` text on ALL images. Empty `alt=""` only for decorative images.
- Lazy loading on all below-the-fold images.
- `@astrojs/sitemap` integration enabled and `site` URL set in `astro.config.mjs`.

---

## ACCESSIBILITY (A11Y)

- **WCAG 2.1 AA** as minimum standard.
- Minimum contrast ratio: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text.
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible (`Tab`, `Enter`, `Space`).
- Focus always visible — never `outline: none` without a visual replacement.
- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons and links.
- `aria-current="page"` on active navigation links.
- Skip link at the top: `<a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only">Skip to content</a>`.
- Semantic roles: `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section aria-labelledby="...">`, `<aside>`.
- Always add `prefers-reduced-motion` fallback for ALL animations.

```css
/* Required in global.css */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

---

## RESPONSIVE DESIGN

- **Mobile-first** — no exceptions.
- Standard Tailwind breakpoints (sm: 640px, md: 768px, lg: 1024px, xl: 1280px).
- Use `clamp()` for fluid typography and spacing.
- Grid layouts with `auto-fill` / `auto-fit` for card components.
- Images must have correct `sizes` attribute.
- Minimum touch target size: 44×44px on mobile.
- Zero horizontal overflow at any breakpoint.
- Test at: 320px, 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1440px.

```css
/* Fluid typography in global.css */
:root {
  --font-size-sm:   clamp(0.875rem, 0.8rem + 0.2vw, 1rem);
  --font-size-base: clamp(1rem, 0.9rem + 0.3vw, 1.125rem);
  --font-size-lg:   clamp(1.125rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 1.375rem);
  --font-size-xl:   clamp(1.5rem, 1.2rem + 1vw, 2rem);
  --font-size-2xl:  clamp(2rem, 1.5rem + 2vw, 3.5rem);
}
```

---

## PERFORMANCE

- **Core Web Vitals targets**: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- Images: WebP/AVIF via `astro:assets`, always define `width` and `height`.
- Fonts: `font-display: swap`, subset only required characters.
- No external CSS frameworks (Bootstrap, etc.) — Tailwind only.
- Lazy load all below-the-fold content.
- Prefetch probable navigation routes with `<link rel="prefetch">`.
- Minimize JS bundle: prefer Astro components over JS-heavy frameworks.

---

## PORTFOLIO SECTIONS

Build these sections in order:

1. **Hero** — Name, title, CTA (view projects / contact me), professional photo
2. **About** — Professional bio, values, what sets you apart
3. **Skills** — Technical and management skills, organized by category
4. **Experience** — Work history timeline (Intel, HP, Soom, Kleeen, TJV)
5. **Projects** — Featured projects grid with tech stack, role, and links
6. **Certifications** — Scrum Master, CAPM, and other credentials
7. **Contact** — Contact form + LinkedIn / GitHub links

---

## NAMING CONVENTIONS

- **Astro components**: PascalCase → `HeroSection.astro`, `ProjectCard.astro`
- **Pages**: kebab-case → `about.astro`, `contact.astro`
- **TypeScript variables**: camelCase → `projectData`, `siteConfig`
- **Constants**: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE → `MAX_FEATURED_PROJECTS`
- **Content files**: kebab-case → `kanban-dashboard.mdx`
- **Assets**: kebab-case → `profile-photo.webp`, `project-kanban-thumbnail.webp`
- **Data service functions**: `get[Resource]()`, `get[Resource]By[Field]()`

---

## REQUIRED CONFIGURATION FILES

- `astro.config.mjs` — with sitemap integration, compress, and `site` URL
- `tailwind.config.mjs` — custom colors, fonts, and breakpoints
- `tsconfig.json` — strict mode, path aliases (`@/components`, `@/layouts`, `@/lib`, `@/types`, `@/data`)
- `.eslintrc.cjs` — TypeScript + Astro rules
- `.prettierrc` — consistent formatting
- `.env.example` — include `PUBLIC_API_URL=` (unused now, ready for Django)
- `public/robots.txt` — allow all, reference sitemap
- `public/sitemap.xml` — auto-generated by `@astrojs/sitemap`

---

## ANTI-PATTERNS — NEVER DO THIS

- ❌ Import data directly into components — always use service functions from `src/lib/data/`
- ❌ Hardcode data inline in components — use `siteConfig.ts` and typed data files
- ❌ Use `any` in TypeScript
- ❌ Use `document.querySelector` in Astro components (use typed `<script>` tags instead)
- ❌ Inline CSS for static values
- ❌ Images without `width`, `height`, and `alt`
- ❌ `!important` in CSS except for documented override utilities
- ❌ External fonts without `preconnect`
- ❌ Pages without a unique meta description
- ❌ Icon-only links without `aria-label`
- ❌ Animations without `prefers-reduced-motion` fallback
- ❌ Data fetching logic inside components or layouts

---

## PREFERRED PATTERNS

- ✅ All data access through `src/lib/data/` service functions — async by default
- ✅ `<Image />` from `astro:assets` for every image
- ✅ Content Collections for long-form project case studies
- ✅ `import.meta.env` for all environment variables
- ✅ `Astro.url` for dynamic canonical URLs
- ✅ Islands Architecture: JS only where truly needed
- ✅ Semantic HTML first, classes second
- ✅ Dark mode with `class` strategy + `prefers-color-scheme` fallback
- ✅ Error boundaries in critical components (especially data-fetching ones)
- ✅ Loading states on all forms and async interactions
- ✅ Type-safe data from day one — types match future Django API response shape

